etimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705184,"age":1,"year":"1096","julianDay":2121366,"title":"The Crusades","description":"A series of religious wars between Christians and Muslims, known as the Crusades, occurred between 1096 and 1291, and played a large role in European Christian dominance in the Middle East.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/middle-ages/crusades","urlTitle":"History - The Crusades","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705185,"age":11,"year":"1106","julianDay":2125018,"title":"The Battle of Tichebray","description":"King Henry I defeated and captured his brother, Robert of Normandy, at the Battle of Tinchebray in 1106. Robert remained in captivity until his death in 1134.","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Robert Rumenel was born about 1095. He married Mrs. Rumenel before 1129, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He died in Kent, England."},"et":{"about 1095–":"umbes 1095–Surnud","1100–Female":"1100–Surnud","1129–1200":"1129–1200","1095–Male":"1095–Surnud","1129":"1129","1106":"1106","about 1095":"umbes 1095","about 1129":"umbes 1129","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","1096":"1096","1095":"1095","before 1129":"enne 1129","England":"England","High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England":"High Wycombe, Buckinghamshire, England","Kent, England":"Kent, England"},"fi":{"about 1095–":"noin 1095–Kuollut","1100–Female":"1100–Kuollut","1129–1200":"1129–1200","1095–Male":"1095–Kuollut","1129":"1129","1106":"1106","about 1095":"noin 1095","about 1129":"noin 1129","1200":"1200","1100":"1100","1096":"1096","1095":"1095","before 1129":"ennen vuotta 1129","England":"